Description: Sandstone stela of Victor; pediment in triangular form enclosing an arch at the top; central panel of incised Coptic text; cross within a wreath below; traces of paint.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Saqqara (Memphis), site of the Monastery of Apa Jeremias
Bibliographic references: British Library 1978 / The Christian Orient (p.41, no.59)
